title: Disney Sues to Keep Complete Rights to Marvel Characters
content: The company filed several lawsuits seeking to invalidate copyright-termination notices served by artists and illustrators involved with creating superheroes like Spider-Man and Thor.

title: ‘Saturday Night Live’ Sets Its Cast as Beck Bennett Departs
content: Other “S.N.L.” veterans including Pete Davidson, Cecily Strong and Kate McKinnon will return to the show, which is adding three new featured players.

title: Why Britain Is Embracing Pounds and Ounces
content: Britain is planning a future that relies on greater usage of its imperial system of weights and measurements. Here’s why it’s happening now.

title: ‘Stairway to Heaven,’ or Dangerous Nuisance? A Hawaii Landmark Is Set to Be Scrapped.
content: Honolulu officials said that maintaining the Haiku Stairs, an illegal hiking trail of 3,922 steps that crosses a mountain range, is too much of a liability.

title: $4 Million Homes in California
content: A French country-style house in San Juan Capistrano, a four-bedroom home in San Francisco and a hillside retreat in Mill Valley.

title: She Bought Her Dream Home. Then a ‘Sovereign Citizen’ Changed the Locks.
content: A New Jersey woman was preyed upon by a fast-growing extremist group that claims its members are sovereign Moors, not bound by U.S. laws.

title: Goldman Sachs, Ozy Media and a $40 Million Conference Call Gone Wrong
content: The digital media company has raised eyebrows for its claims about its audience size for years. Then came the strange voice on the phone.

title: Cancer Without Chemotherapy: ‘A Totally Different World’
content: A growing number of cancer patients, especially those with breast and lung cancers, are being spared the dreaded treatment in favor of other options.

title: These Health Care Workers Would Rather Get Fired Than Get Vaccinated
content: Monday is the vaccination deadline for New York State health care workers. Thousands of refusers have failed to meet it.
